text.section:
A licensee shall disclose a record that is sought:
By the staff of the licensee to carry out a purpose for which the record is kept;
By any other person who provides or coordinates services in accordance with the individual's plan of habilitation;
By the Director or a designee of the Director; and
By a person to further the purposes of:
A medical review committee;
An accreditation board or commission;
A licensing agency that is authorized by statute to review records;
A court order;
A representative of the Division of Reimbursement of the Department;
An auditor of the Department;
An auditor of the Office of Legislative Audits of the Department of Legislative Services; or
The Clients' Rights Committee of the licensee unless the individual with developmental disability objects.
